    "authority": "Owns the only public coding-session application orchestration and validation boundary behind explicit repository, code-engine, event, engine-validation, project-execution-scope, and internal native-session reader ports. Provider histories are reconciled into durable coding sessions before public pagination; session persistence and client input never authorize a filesystem path; route adapters own HTTP extraction and response mapping; SQLx repositories own persistence."
